('NPS Photo', 'Natchez Trace Parkway in Early Fall', 'A slightly curvy section of the Natchez Trace Parkway in Early Fall', 'The Natchez Trace Parkway commemorates a historic travel route that helped build the young United States. The Parkway 444 miles, with plenty of stops to allow you to explore some of the history or enjoy the scenery along the way.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C80016C-1DD8-B71B-0B91B2FA75DF0C02.jpg', 1838),
('NPS Photo', 'Double Arch Bridge over Birdsong Hollow (milepost 438) on the Natchez Trace Parkway', 'View of the Double Arch Bridge from Birdsong Hollow', 'The elegant Double Arch Bridge won the Presidential Award for Design Excellence in 1995. It spans Birdsong Hollow and Tennessee Highway 96. To see it from below, take the TN 96 exit and stop at the pulloff before you get to the highway.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C7FFB07-1DD8-B71B-0B35C15D0834A556.jpg', 1839),
