('NPS / Cindy Jacoby', 'Yosemite Falls on a Winter Morning', 'Two tall waterfalls flowing down snow covered granite walls.', 'Yosemite Falls will sometimes only trickle at the end of summer, but wet winters can rejuvenate the flow.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C84CC4C-1DD8-B71B-0BE967E5E5D93F25.jpg', 2776),
('NPS', 'Glen Aulin', 'Mountains reflecting in water', 'Glen Auilin is one of five High Sierra Camps, located in the Yosemite high country.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C84C82D-1DD8-B71B-0B8D6902B62369E2.jpg', 2777),
('NPS / Cindy Jacoby', 'Giant Sequoia Trees in the Mariposa Grove of Giant Sequoias', 'Cluster of tall trees with cloudy sky.', 'Yosemite National Park\'s massive giant sequoias (Sequoiadendron giganteum) live in three groves in the park. The most famous of these is the Mariposa Grove, which contains about 500 mature giant sequoias.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C8560E1-1DD8-B71B-0BD3183636F4B861.jpg', 2778),
('NPS', 'Tenaya Lake at Sunset', 'Mountains surrounding a lake.', 'Tenaya Lake is a favorite place to stop along the Tioga Road in summer.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C84C97E-1DD8-B71B-0B5DD2112C58C175.jpg', 2779),
('NPS / Cindy Jacoby', 'Half Dome', 'Granite dome with trace amounts of snow.', 'Half Dome is one of the most recognizable granitic formations in the world.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C84CF74-1DD8-B71B-0B9C7FF83F7C68EB.jpg', 2780),
('NPS Photo/ Christine Fey', 'El Capitan', 'El Capitan and reflection in Merced River with some low clouds', 'El Capitan rises over 3,000 feet above the floor of Yosemite Valley.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/058C8410-D5BA-32F4-BC468014AF42CB0B.jpg', 2781),
('NPS Photo', 'View of Yosemite Valley in Winter', 'El Capitan on left, Cathedral Rocks on the right, all covered in snow, low clouds and sun', 'A rewarding view of Yosemite Valley in winter as seen from Tunnel View.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/232C02DC-BE31-0C6D-E1E2D2FB1EE7E251.jpg', 2782),
('NPS Photo', 'Yucca House Spring', 'Cattails with mesa in background.', 'Cattails define marshy locations watered by springs.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C7C2020-1DD8-B71B-0B9F3E84D4AE2CD0.jpg', 2783),
('NPS Photo', 'View of Mesa Verde from Yucca House', 'View of Mesa Verde landform', 'View of Mesa Verde above from Yucca House in the valley below.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C7C2179-1DD8-B71B-0BD549D711B7C146.jpg', 2784),
('NPS Photo', 'Walls of the Yucca House Pueblo', 'Masonry walls seen through shrubbery', 'Ancient walls of Yucca House still standing today.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C7C238F-1DD8-B71B-0B00D1C3C27BFBFB.jpg', 2785),
('NPS Photo', 'Ancestral Puebloan Wall at Yucca House', 'Close up view of an ancient wall at Yucca House', 'View of an Ancestral Puebloan wall still standing at Yucca House.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C7C24F8-1DD8-B71B-0B4DA773A67908B3.jpg', 2786),
('NPS Photo', 'Yucca House in Context', 'View of  ancient wall in the center of agricultural land surrounding it.', 'The Yucca House archeological site is surrounded by agricultural land today.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C7C2736-1DD8-B71B-0BF4D35DE98A58DB.jpg', 2787),
('NPS Photo / Josh Spice', 'Aerial view of the Yukon River', 'Aerial view of the Yukon River during fall colors', 'The Yukon River is a vast body of water that has carved its path into the landscape over millions of years.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/5441BF50-05AD-F33E-6A0339476B5B18EF.jpg', 2788),
('NPS Photo / Josh Spice', 'Coal Creek Dredge', 'Historic Coal Creek Dredge', 'The historic Coal Creek Dredge sits nonoperational at its original site, near Slaven\'s Roadhouse', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C7A625C-1DD8-B71B-0B937F599D9D10DF.jpg', 2789),
('NPS Photo / Greg Kinman', 'Eagle Visitor Center', 'Eagle Visitor Center in front of Eagle Bluff', 'The Eagle Visitor Center sits atop a small bluff overlooking the Yukon River.', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/3C7A6453-1DD8-B71B-0BD5799A0348C713.jpg', 2790),
('NPS Photo / Josh Spice', 'Slaven\'s Roadhouse during fall colors', 'Slaven\'s Roadhouse during fall colors', 'A historic roadhouse and public use cabin on the Yukon River', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/56A9969F-9BE7-F7A4-2DF42106328FEFBE.jpg', 2791),
('NPS Photo / Josh Spice', 'Calico Bluff and the Yukon River', 'Calico Bluff rising above the Yukon River that also winds into the distance behind the bluff', 'Calico Bluff, showing 4 million years of rock layers, rises above the Yukon River and is one of many bluffs along the 130 miles of river in the preserve', 'https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/structured_data/576A1897-A20F-B183-CE6A8AB15207E519.jpg', 2792),
